<section xml:id="C29.S14">
<title>Orthogonality</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C29.S14.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C29.S14.p1.s1">
Lamé polynomials are orthogonal in two ways.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C29.S14.p1.s2">
First, the orthogonality relations (29.3.19)apply; see §29.12(i).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C29.S14.p1.s3">
Secondly, the system of functions <Math equation-number="29.14.1" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E1">f_{n}^{m}(s,t)=\mathit{uE}^{m}_{2n}\left(s,k^{2}\right)\mathit{uE}^{m}_{2n} \left(\!K\!+\mathrm{i}t,k^{2}\right), if n=0,1,2,\dots, m=0,1,\dots,n,</Math> is orthogonal and complete with respect to the inner product <Math equation-number="29.14.2" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E2">\langle g,h\rangle=\int_{0}^{\!K\!}\!\!\int_{0}^{\!{K^{\prime}}\!}w(s,t)g(s,t) h(s,t)\mathrm{d}t\mathrm{d}s,</Math> where <Math equation-number="29.14.3" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E3">w(s,t)={\operatorname{sn}^{2}}\left(\!K\!+\mathrm{i}t,k\right)-{\operatorname{ sn}^{2}}\left(s,k\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C29.S14.p2">

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C29.S14.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C29.S14.p3.s1">
Each of the following seven systems is orthogonal and complete with respect to the inner product (29.14.2):
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C29.S14.p3.s2">
<Math equation-number="29.14.4" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E4">\mathit{sE}^{m}_{2n+1}\left(s,k^{2}\right)\mathit{sE}^{m}_{2n+1}\left(\!K\!+ \mathrm{i}t,k^{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="29.14.5" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E5">\mathit{cE}^{m}_{2n+1}\left(s,k^{2}\right)\mathit{cE}^{m}_{2n+1}\left(\!K\!+ \mathrm{i}t,k^{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="29.14.6" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E6">\mathit{dE}^{m}_{2n+1}\left(s,k^{2}\right)\mathit{dE}^{m}_{2n+1}\left(\!K\!+ \mathrm{i}t,k^{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="29.14.7" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E7">\mathit{scE}^{m}_{2n+2}\left(s,k^{2}\right)\mathit{scE}^{m}_{2n+2}\left(\!K\!+ \mathrm{i}t,k^{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="29.14.8" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E8">\mathit{sdE}^{m}_{2n+2}\left(s,k^{2}\right)\mathit{sdE}^{m}_{2n+2}\left(\!K\!+ \mathrm{i}t,k^{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="29.14.9" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E9">\mathit{cdE}^{m}_{2n+2}\left(s,k^{2}\right)\mathit{cdE}^{m}_{2n+2}\left(\!K\!+ \mathrm{i}t,k^{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="29.14.10" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E10">\mathit{scdE}^{m}_{2n+3}\left(s,k^{2}\right)\mathit{scdE}^{m}_{2n+3}\left(\!K \!+\mathrm{i}t,k^{2}\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C29.S14.p3.s3">
In each system <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C29.S14.p3.m1">n</Math> ranges over all nonnegative integers and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C29.S14.p3.m2">m=0,1,\dots,n</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C29.S14.p3.s4">
When combined, all eight systems (29.14.1) and (29.14.4)–(29.14.10) form an orthogonal and complete system with respect to the inner product <Math equation-number="29.14.11" mode="display" xml:id="C29.S14.E11">\langle g,h\rangle=\int_{0}^{4\!K\!}\!\!\int_{0}^{2\!{K^{\prime}}\!}w(s,t)g(s, t)h(s,t)\mathrm{d}t\mathrm{d}s,</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C29.S14.p3.m3">w(s,t)</Math> given by (29.14.3).
</sentence>

</para>

 
</section>
